author: photowanderer
body:
"Shares of oil giant Saudi Aramco (2222.SE) fell 1.7% to their lowest level since listing last month ..." 

Me: are we calling 1.7% a plunge? 

Clicks the article: "The Kuwaiti index, the best performer in the region in 2019, was down nearly 4.1%, while Saudi stocks .TASI plunged 2.2%. Dubai stocks .DFMGI were down 3.1% and the Abu Dhabi index .ADI fell 1.41%."

Me: ah okay

author: sofreshnsogreengreen
body:
ATTENTION

small cap cloud revival part 6 appears to be in effect

the cloud has been fighting off gay feelings from chemtrails since august '19. most have been bottomed out for \~2 months at least

starting to see some strength this past week. we finna take off with this new year

buy long dated calls soon on fsly, crwd, net, ftnt, panw, etc

author: googlme
body: for example ftnt and panw are both better investments in my opinion.

author: roochenz
body: CrowdStrike, FireEye, Palo Alto, Fortinet are all deployed in the fed government in some capacity.

author: UABeeezy
body: Cyber security is a good play as well. CRWD and FTNT both saw good movement today.

author: sofreshnsogreengreen
body:
cloud in general is looking back on the menu. in fact, i'm somehow least confident in crwd just cause i believe more in the tech/offerings of others in the sector. fsly, net, ddog, cybr, panw. ftnt is high but has been slaying

i think i'm gonna look for entry on some crwd calls too though and look for it to hit \~60
